cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NA, cs.CV 

The paper deals with the problem of estimating an unknown high-dimensional signal from noisy linear measurements, assuming a group-sparse structure in a known dictionary. This problem is related to compressed sensing (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SI), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses an application of the group Lasso approach to structural health monitoring, which is related to signal processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.SI, followed by cs.NA and cs.CV.
